annotationA: Nitrilase and fragile histidine triad fusion protein NitFhit; Cleaves A-5'-PPP-5'A to yield AMP and ADP
annotationB: NADPH:adrenodoxin oxidoreductase, mitochondrial; Defective in the avoidance of repellents is an enzyme associated with steroid hormone synthesis and required for normal olfactory behavior.  Some mutants show widespread degeneration of adult nervous system; Belongs to the ferredoxin--NADP reductase type 1 family
